.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
Structure representing a single level in the stack\&. Has a pointer to the level above and below itself and a pointer to a generic blob of data associated with this level\&. 
.SH "Field Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "struct \fBstack_level\fP* above"
Pointer to the level above this one\&. If NULL, then this level is the top of the stack\&. If above is non-NULL, this level \fImay\fP be the top, but all that can be guaranteed is that there are other allocated but potentially unused levels above this one\&. 
.SS "struct \fBstack_level\fP* below"
Pointer to the level below this one\&. If NULL, then this level is the bottom\&. 
.SS "void* data"
Pointer to some data associated with this level\&. User is responsible for knowing what to cast the \fRvoid\fP \fR*\fP pointer into\&. 

